@@TJvLinkedControls.RestoreEnabled
Summary
  Specifies whether the enabled state of linked controls are restored when the linked control is
  removed or replaced.
Description
  Use RestoreEnabled to specify whether the Enabled state of linked controls is restored when the
  linked Control is removed from the list or replaced by another Control. When RestoreEnabled is
  true, the Enabled state is set to the same value as it was at the time the control was assigned. If
  false, the control's current Enabled state is left untouched.

